name: Test Office 365 Network Access
description: Tests TCP connection to Microsoft Office 365 services specified in input parameters. For domain ranges only parent domains are considered, for IP ranges a set of random IPs are considered.

inputs.description: Maximum random delay set to avoid overloading server hosting virtual machines. Provide number of seconds less than 600
inputs.name: MaximumDelayInSeconds

inputs.description: Mandatory parameter of an Office 365 Organization name owned by a customer
inputs.name: TenantName

inputs.description: Mandatory parameter of an Office 365 service instance. Accepted value is one of the following ('Worldwide', 'China', 'Germany', 'USGovDoD', 'USGovGCCHigh'). By default 'Worldwide' option is used
inputs.name: Instance

inputs.description: Mandatory parameter to test access to specific applications. Accepted values separated by comma are ('Common', 'Exchange', 'SharePoint', 'Skype'). 'Common' service area items are a prerequisite for all other service areas, therefore tests will always include them
inputs.name: ServiceArea

inputs.description: Timeout value for each test connection attempt. Provide number of seconds between (1-10)
inputs.name: ConnectionTimeout

outputs.description: Confirmation if network access to all specified Microsoft services is allowed
outputs.name: RequiredConnectivityAvailable

outputs.description: List of services reported as failing to connect
outputs.name: FailingServices

outputs.description: List of domains reported as failing to connect
outputs.name: FailingDomains

outputs.description: List of IP addresses or IP ranges reported as failing to connect
outputs.name: FailingIPRanges
